Reasoning: The paper discusses the learning of objectives for autonomous systems (robots) from human behavior, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of game theory in analyzing the interaction between the robot and human suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of human behavior, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL).
